===Anime===
A 12-episode [[anime]] television series by [[Doga Kobo]] aired from January 9<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-11-17/bushiroad-announces-luck-and-logic-original-anime-project/.95478|title=Bushiroad Announces ''Luck and Logic'' Original Anime Project|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 17, 2015|accessdate=January 5, 2016}}</ref> to March 26, 2016. The opening theme is "STORY" by [[Kenshō Ono]] and the ending theme is {{Nihongo|"Meiyaku no Kanata"|盟約の彼方}} by [[Emi Nitta]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-18/luck-and-logic-anime-promo-features-kensho-ono-opening-theme/.96690|title=''Luck and Logic'' Anime Promo Features Kensho Ono's Opening Theme|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 18, 2015|accessdate=January 5, 2016}}</ref>

A new 12-episode television series titled {{nihongo|''Hina Logi ~from Luck & Logic~''|ひなろじ〜from Luck & Logic〜}} aired from July 1<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-30/bushiroad-luck-and-logic-card-game-gets-hina-logi-tv-anime-in-summer/.111614|title=Bushiroad's Luck & Logic Card Game Gets Hina Logi TV Anime in Summer|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 30, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-30/bushiroad-streams-promo-video-for-hina-logi-from-luck-and-logic-tv-series/.111621|title=Bushiroad Streams Promo Video for Hina Logi: From Luck & Logic TV Series|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 30, 2017|accessdate=January 30, 2017}}</ref><ref name="July premiere"/> to September 23, 2017. [[Funimation]] has licensed this both series in North America.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-01/funimation-reveals-summer-simuldub-lineup/.118312|title=Funimation Reveals Summer Simuldub Lineup|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 2, 2017|accessdate=July 2, 2017}}</ref>

